<!-- pstack:start v0.1 -->
## pstack

Use pstack skills for product-management work — vision, PRDs, design briefs, persona-driven reviews, CEO/CPO challenges, and self-improvement workflows.

**Available commands:**
- /vision — create or refine a product vision doc
- /prd — draft a rigorous PRD grounded in the vision
- /design-brief — produce a design brief from a PRD
- /critique — score any artifact against its rubric; list gaps
- /cagan-review — Marty Cagan's lens (four risks, outcomes > output)
- /shreyas-review — Shreyas Doshi's lens (LNO, high agency, execution quality)
- /lenny-review — Lenny Rachitsky's lens (growth loops, activation, retention)
- /bhaskar-review — heart-centric, purpose-led, ikigai-anchored lens
- /challenge — CEO/CPO-level provocation grounded in current project (daily)
- /onboard — seed ~/.config/pstack/user-profile.yaml for cross-project personalization
- /pstack-status — dashboard across all projects (rubric scores, staleness, last challenge)
- /pstack-upgrade — pull latest pstack + re-run setup + diff new skills
- /pstack-help — context-aware next-action recommendation (reads last-session.md)
- /pstack-learn — distill feedback logs + user edits into framework improvement proposals

**Conventions:**
- Generators (/vision, /prd, /design-brief) run an internal draft→critique→revise loop before surfacing output. User sees only post-revision work.
- Generators write to ./pstack-workspace/<slug>/ with numbered filenames: 00-vision.md, 02-prd.md, 03-design-brief.md.
- Each generator reads prior artifacts and knowledge/INDEX.md before interviewing — never starts cold.
- Reviewers write to pstack-workspace/<slug>/reviews/ — they never mutate source artifacts.
- /challenge appends to pstack-workspace/<slug>/CHALLENGES.md (gitignored by default).
- /pstack-help reads ~/.config/pstack/last-session.md — always run it when resuming a session.
- Attribution footers mandatory on all output that cites frameworks or personas.
<!-- pstack:end v0.1 -->
